  "query": "hmmm.. after reviewing the current arch decisions, I think reconsideing removing auto_enroll.  Why? The per call lookup is ACTUALLY a security capability that I want to retain, at the current time, it is not useful.  The problem it putting it back in later, in my mind becomes HARDER.   This scope becomes an ADDITION of the LLM identity level identity check, if it does not exist, it does not allow the LLM to connect (I'm not sure I like, it doesn't allow the server to start either.. because in a centralized HTTP scenario, the server might be responding to 1 repo properly configured with Oauth, but disallow any other).  I'm still actually thinking about the agent_id field and how to best leverage it, but I don't want to eliminate my ability to do something with it.  I recognize its not a security capability today, but I feel like this may be a focus longer term to resolve... therefore, I don't want to elimminate this capability",
